e | Terminate |\n| 340 | The Riding House Cafe | Facilities | 264.82 | Food, beverage or hospitality services for office | Terminate |\n| 341 | The Virtual Legal Counsel Ltd | Legal | 4,800.30 | Virtual in-house legal counsel advisory services | Terminate |\n| 342 | Thomas Mansfield Solicitors Limited | Legal | 1,135.05 | UK employment law firm for HR and tribunal matters | Terminate |\n| 343 | Tiganda J.D.O.O. | Facilities | 431.71 | Croatian local vendor providing miscellaneous services | Terminate |\n| 344 | Till Trade D.O.O. | Facilities | 93.07 | Croatian local vendor providing miscellaneous services | Terminate |\n| 345 | Time Out Group | Marketing | 920.47 | Media advertising in Time Out city guides | Terminate |\n| 346 | Tm Forum | Legal | 510.05 | Industry association membership for telecoms standards | Terminate |\n| 347 | Tmforum | Legal | 57,560.43 | Industry association membership for telecoms standards | Terminate |\n| 348 | T-Mobile | Engineering | 3,357.46 | Mobile telecommunications and connectivity provider | Consolidate |\n| 349 | Tog Uk Properties Limited | Facilities | 263,821.16 | Managed office space and co-working facilities provider | Optimize |\n| 350 | Tp Prime D.O.O. | Facilities | 13,785.41 | Croatian local vendor providing miscellaneous services | Terminate |\n| 351 | Trans-Agram Obrt Za Dostavu | Facilities | 580.72 | Croatian local vendor providing miscellaneous services | Terminate |\n| 352 | Treci Posao D.O.O. | Facilities | 307.39 | Croatian local vendor providing miscellaneous services | Terminate |\n| 353 | Trello | Engineering | 6,673.88 | Visual project and task management board tool | Consolidate |\n| 354 | Trending Technology Services Gmbh | Engineering | 961.34 | IT services and solutions provider | Terminate |\n| 355 | Trocadero (London) Hotel Ltd | Facilities | 3,867.51 | Food, beverage or hospitality services for office | Terminate |\n| 356 | Uber *Eats | Facilities | 49.76 | Food, beverage or hospitality services for office | Terminate |\n| 357 | Uberflip | Marketing | 26,090.98 | Content experience platform for demand generation | Consolidate |\n| 358 | Uk Postbox Limited | Facilities | 670.13 | Virtual mailbox and postal address services UK | Terminate |\n| 359 | United Flow Ltd (The Goodness Project) | G&A | 2,744.38 | Low-spend vendor with limited strategic value | Terminate |\n| 360 | Uptime Robot Service Provider Ltd | Engineering | 78.33 | Website uptime monitoring and alerting service | Consolidate |\n| 361 | Urbani Eventi D.O.O. | Facilities | 850.65 | Croatian local vendor providing miscellaneous services | Terminate |\n| 362 | Ustanova Za Medicinu Rada I Sporta Dr. Novacki | HR | 20.27 | Occupational health and medical services Croatia | Consolidate |\n| 363 | Ustanova Za Zdravstvenu Skrb P.P. | HR | 130.85 | Occupational health and medical services Croatia | Consolidate |\n| 364 | Vector Capital Management Lp | Finance | 32,426.73 | Private equity investment management advisory | Terminate |\n| 365 | Veniture D.O.O. | Facilities | 39,342.12 | Croatian local vendor providing miscellaneous services | Terminate |\n| 366 | Visalogic Limited | Legal | 11,240.71 | Immigration and visa management services | Consolidate |\n| 367 | Vistaprint | Marketing | 129.93 | Printed marketing materials and stationery | Terminate |\n| 368 | Vitality Works | HR | 181.53 | Employee wellness and occupational health services | Terminate |\n| 369 | Vivat Fina Vina D.O.O. | Facilities | 466.62 | Food, beverage or hospitality services for office | Terminate |\n| 370 | Vodafone (Australian) | Engineering | 3,671.66 | Mobile and broadband connectivity services | Consolidate |\n| 371 | Weking D.O.O. | Facilities | 144,093.20 | Croatian local vendor providing miscellaneous services | Terminate |\n| 372 | Westbrook Advisers | Finance | 15,360.38 | Financial advisory and consulting services | Terminate |\n| 373 | Wework Singapore Pte. Ltd. | Facilities | 64,373.36 | Flexible co-working office space provider | Terminate |\n| 374 | Winmaxi Tours & Travels | Facilities | 1,001.36 | Corporate travel and tour services in India | Terminate |\n| 375 | Wolt Enterprises Oy | Facilities | 61.74 | Food, beverage or hospitality services for office | Terminate |\n| 376 | Work Easy Space Solutions Private Limited | Facilities | 14,913.21 | Managed office and co-working spaces in India | Terminate |\n| 377 | Workato, Inc. | Engineering | 16,101.03 | Enterprise automation and integration platform | Consolidate |\n| 378 | Xenon Savjetovanje D.O.O. | Facilities | 164.02 | Croatian local vendor providing miscellaneous services | Terminate |\n| 379 | Yellow Submarine D.O.O. | Facilities | 486.21 | Croatian local vendor providing miscellaneous services | Terminate |\n| 380 | Yoxel, Inc | Engineering | 2,043.60 | API integration and data synchronization services | Terminate |\n| 381 | Zagrebački Holding D.O.O. | Facilities | 142.83 | Croatian local vendor providing miscellaneous services | Terminate |\n| 382 | Zagrebtower D.O.O. | Facilities | 183,754.42 | Zagreb Tower office premises rent and services | Optimize |\n| 383 | Zapier Inc. | Engineering | 166.79 | Workflow automation and app integration platform | Consolidate |\n| 384 | Zettanet | Engineering | 183.37 | Network management and connectivity services | Consolidate |\n| 385 | Zivi Napitak D.O.O. | Facilities | 3,699.58 | Food, beverage or hospitality services for office | Terminate |\n| 386 | Zuric I Partneri Odvjetnicko Drustvo D.O.O. | Legal | 24,135.44 | Croatian law firm for corporate and commercial law | Terminate |\n\n---\n\n## Top 3 Opportunities\n**Total rows: 5** (4 content rows + 1 blank)\n\n**Header:** `[blank] | Opportunity | Explanation | Estimated Annual Savings (USD)`\n\n| # | Opportunity | Explanation | Est. Annual Savings |\n|---|------------|-------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Renegotiate Salesforce UK Enterprise Contract | Salesforce at $3.1M is 39.5% of total vendor spend (Parallel Strategic). Right-size unused licences and renegotiate multi-year enterprise pricing tiers. 15% reduction delivers $468K annually; renewal window is critical leverage. | $467,584 |\n| 2 | Execute Long-tail Vendor Termination Program | 267 Terminate-rated vendors hold $1.6M in redundant spend (Immediate). Cancel Score-1 SaaS subscriptions first; issue notices for contract vendors. 10% realisation in 90 days yields $163K with minimal operational risk. | $163,215 |\n| 3 | Consolidate Co-working and Office Space Portfolio | $828K fragmented across 8 co-working vendors; high duplication (Parallel Strategic). Consolidate to 1–2 preferred operators; renegotiate volume-based pricing. 15% reduction through preferred-operator terms saves $124K annually. | $124,175 |\n\n**Total estimated savings: $755,000**\n\n---\n\n## Methodology\n**Total rows: 28**\n\n**APPROACH:**\n- Structured the analysis end to end across 16 sequential steps, from workbook inspection through to executive memo generation\n- Reviewed the full vendor dataset to understand spend distribution, identify the top-10 vendors by spend, and quantify long-tail exposure\n- Identified workbook structure and template constraints upfront — including allowed departments, recommendation values, and cell-level write rules — before writing any data\n- Sequenced the analysis in four logical phases: inspection and data understanding → vendor classification and categorisation → opportunity identification and prioritisation → recommendations and documentation\n\n**METHODOLOGY:**\n- Data review: vendor spend data sourced directly from workbook; total spend and concentration analysed across all 386 vendors\n- Spend concentration analysis: top 10 vendors ranked by spend; long-tail vendors below $50K identified for rationalisation\n- Vendor categorisation: service categories and departments assigned using domain knowledge and spend pattern analysis\n- Service overlap identification: duplicate service categories detected; consolidation candidates flagged\n- Cost optimisation framework: Terminate / Consolidate / Optimize decision rules applied per vendor based on strategic value, spend level, and category overlap\n- Opportunity prioritisation: top 3 opportunities selected using multi-factor evaluation across financial impact, execution effort, business risk, and time to value\n\n**PROMPTS:**\n- A 16-step structured prompt workflow was designed and executed sequentially via Claude Code CLI\n- Each step had a single clearly scoped analytical task: inspect, classify, score, identify, validate, or document\n- Key prompts covered: workbook inspection, vendor classification, duplicate detection, strategic scoring, opportunity identification, methodology documentation, and executive memo generation\n- All prompts enforced strict output format rules: allowed departments, recommendation values, cell-level write constraints, and sheet-level write guards\n- Prompts were passed to Claude Code CLI via stdin pipe in non-interactive mode using `printf`\n\n**TOOLS:**\n- Claude Code CLI (Anthropic): AI reasoning and analytical tasks across all 16 steps\n- Node.js with xlsx (SheetJS) library: Excel workbook read and write operations throughout the pipeline\n- Python with openpyxl: post-pipeline formatting restoration from the original template\n- Bash orchestration script: step sequencing, checkpoint and resume logic, and log capture across all pipeline stages\n\n---\n\n## CEOCFO Recommendations\n**Total rows: 3**\n\n**Row 0 (prompt/instruction cell):**\n> \"Please prepare a short memo (maximum 1 page) summarizing your findings and recommendations to the CEO and CFO. Please keep in mind that these are busy people; position your points accordingly, focus on what really matters, and do not exceed the number of pages; do not overemphasize things that are obvious to them but also keep in mind they have many things going on and may not remember immediately certain points. Please provide a Google Doc link to your memo below\"\n\n**Row 1:** *(blank — Google Doc link field, not filled)*\n\n**Row 2 (memo content):**\n\n---\n**MEMORANDUM**\nTO: Chief Executive Officer | Chief Financial Officer\nFROM: R. Jegadeswari, Strategic Procurement Lead\nDATE: 22 March 2026\nRE: Vendor Spend Rationalisation — Findings & Recommendations\n\n**1. VENDOR SPEND OVERVIEW**\n- 386 active vendors | Total LTM spend: $7,887,360\n- Breakdown: 265 vendors for Termination ($1,475,052, 18.7%); 22 for Optimisation ($4,899,490, 62.1%); 99 for Consolidation ($1,512,819, 19.2%)\n- Top 10 vendors account for 63.9% of total spend — acute concentration risk\n\n**3. TOP 3 OPPORTUNITIES**\n- Opportunities structured across Immediate and Parallel Strategic tracks to maximise speed, feasibility, and minimise operational risk\n- Renegotiate Salesforce UK Enterprise Contract: right-size licences and renegotiate multi-year pricing using $3.1M volume leverage — est. $468,000\n- Execute Long-tail Vendor Termination Program: cancel 265 low-value SaaS subscriptions and non-renew tail contracts immediately — est. $163,000\n- Consolidate Co-working and Office Space Portfolio: consolidate 8 co-working vendors to 1–2 preferred operators; renegotiate volume-based terms — est. $124,000\n- Total estimated savings: $755,000\n\n**4. ESTIMATED SAVINGS SUMMARY**\n- Total identified savings: $755,000 (9.6% of total LTM spend)\n- Year 1 conservatively realisable: $453,000 (60% of identified savings)\n- Payback on implementation effort: under 6 months\n\n**5. IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP**\n- Month 1–2: Terminate 265 low-value vendors; close duplicate AP entities\n- Month 3–4: Consolidate co-working portfolio to two preferred operators\n- Month 4–6: Launch Salesforce renegotiation with executive sponsorship\n- Month 6+: Execute insurance and audit consolidation; embed vendor governance\n\n**6. RISKS AND MITIGATIONS**\n- Service disruption: stagger terminations; confirm substitutes before exit\n- Negotiation failure: engage Salesforce pre-renewal; deploy volume leverage early\n- Vendor concentration: Salesforce at 39.5% — run parallel CRM benchmark if talks stall\n\nRecommended next step: CPO to engage Salesforce UK in Q2 2026 ahead of the enterprise renewal window — leveraging the $3.1M contract volume to negotiate a minimum 15% reduction and multi-year lock-in; this single action unlocks $468,000 annually and directly addresses the portfolio's most acute concentration risk.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of what was found:**\n- The workbook has 7 sheets total (the 4 requested plus Config, First Quick Analysis, and STEP08 Strategic Scores)\n- **Vendor Analysis Assessment**: 386 vendor rows fully populated with name, department, cost, description, and Terminate/Consolidate/Optimize recommendation; the 6th column (DERIVED-Spend Category) is blank for all rows\n- **Top 3 Opportunities**: 3 opportunities fully populated with explanations and savings estimates ($467,584 + $163,215 + $124,175 = $755,000 total)\n- **Methodology**: 28 rows covering approach, methodology, prompts, and tools — all populated\n- **CEOCFO Recommendations**: Memo is written in the cell (Row 2); the Google Doc link field (Row 1) is blank/not provided"}],"totalDurationMs":351259,"totalTokens":46389,"totalToolUseCount":8,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2634,"cache_read_input_tokens":27469,"output_tokens":16285,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2634},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
